Looking at Timestamps
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

    >>> fd = nltk.FreqDist()
    >>> for entry in lexicon:
    ...     date = entry.findtext('dt')
    ...     if date:
    ...         (day, month, year) = string.split(date, '/')
    ...         fd.inc((month, year))
    >>> for time in fd.sorted():
    ...     print time[0], time[1], ':', fd[time]
